Save findings to Docs/ai-improvement-ideas.md:
1) Exercise demonstration: how to show users form videos/images for exercises
2) Image-based food logging: photo → describe → log (needs vision model)
3) Voice input: iOS speech-to-text → AI chat → hands-free food logging
4) Weekly AI summary: background task generates weekly health insight notification
5) Fine-tuning: create health Q&A dataset, fine-tune for better domain answers
6) Model distillation: train SmolLM2-360M to match Qwen quality for faster inference
7) On-device embeddings: MiniLM for semantic food search
8) Apple Neural Engine: CoreML conversion for ANE acceleration

=== HOW TO WORK ===

- Check .claude-stop status before every cycle
- Commit after each meaningful improvement
- Run tests after every change
- Build after every change
- Push to git frequently
- When stuck, research on the web
- When something isn't clear, don't break existing functionality

Status options:
- RUNNING: continue the loop
- STOP: finish current work, commit, halt
- PAUSE: commit and wait for instructions
- REDIRECT: read Direction field, apply changes, set back to RUNNING
